task.specification:
let us make an interesting function that takes the camera images and adds it to itself flipped left to right, and ensure that the range of values is the same as in the input images.
the input of the function are three numpy arrays that are images: img_camera, img_mask_segmentation, img_diffusion, which are all float32. we need one numpy array as output. it has to pass the existing test. make sure the function name is called 'process'.
